org.jacktheclipper.frontend.model

Class ShortArticle

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jacktheclipper.frontend.model.ShortArticle
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Article

    public class ShortArticle
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a short version of an article. Thus the text of it is limited by the backend. This is used to show the content of an user feed.

      • publishedAsGermanDate

        public java.lang.String publishedAsGermanDate()
        Formats the published as a german date. This allows the feedOverview page to be displayed entirely in german.
        Returns:
        The published field formatted as a german date. With the month written out. E. g. 'Mai' instead of '05'.
